<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38213f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38213f">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38213f"> 213(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> appropriate lyric</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The catechumens, thirty-three in all, consist of five families and three or four &ldquo;oddments&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The missionary takes the right hand of each adult, hardened by toil to the consistency of a boot-sole, as he receives him or her into the congregation of Christ&apos;s flock <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> After all have been baptized an <mark>appropriate lyric</mark> is sung, while the new Christians and the rest of the congregation turn and settle into their accustomed places. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c08040i" href="c8all.htm#c08040i">VI.C.08:040(i)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
